hh3cFdmi.name: hh3cFdmi

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

hh3cFdmi.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip: 100085
hh3cFdmi.description: This MIB module is for monitoring Fabric Device Management Interface (FDMI) related entities. This MIB module defines objects for managing the devices such as Host Bus Adapter (HBA). It provides device information which has been registered with an Fibre Channel (FC) fabric using FDMI. For more information on FDMI, refer to Fibre Channel Generic Services-6 Section 6.7 : Fabric Device Management Interface.

hh3cFdmiHbaInfoTable.name: hh3cFdmiHbaInfoTable
hh3cFdmiHbaInfoTable.description: This table lists all the HBAs registered with the Fabric Device Management Interface.

hh3cFdmiHbaInfoEntry.name: hh3cFdmiHbaInfoEntry
hh3cFdmiHbaInfoEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table. It provides information that has been registered with FDMI by a HBA, on the Virtual Storage Area Network (VSAN) where the registration was received. If the HBA has registered some but not all of the information represented by the columnar objects in this table, then the value of the unregistered objects will be either the zero-length string (for string-based objects) or the zero value (for integer-based objects).

hh3cFdmiHbaInfoId.name: hh3cFdmiHbaInfoId
hh3cFdmiHbaInfoId.reference: Fibre Channel Generic Services-6 Rev 9.4 Section 6.7.4.5.1 .
hh3cFdmiHbaInfoId.description: The World Wide Name (WWN) of this HBA.

hh3cFdmiHbaInfoNodeName.description: The WWN of the node containing this HBA.

hh3cFdmiHbaInfoOptROMVer.description: The version of the Option ROM or the BIOS of this HBA.

hh3cFdmiHbaInfoFwVer.description: The version of the firmware executed by this HBA.

hh3cFdmiHbaInfoOSInfo.reference: Fibre Channel Generic Services-6 Rev 9.4 Section 6.7.4.4.2.12 .
hh3cFdmiHbaInfoOSInfo.description: The type and version of the operating system controlling this HBA.

hh3cFdmiHbaInfoMaxCTPayload.name: hh3cFdmiHbaInfoMaxCTPayload
hh3cFdmiHbaInfoMaxCTPayload.reference: Fibre Channel Generic Services-6 Rev 9.4 Section 6.7.4.4.2.13 .
hh3cFdmiHbaInfoMaxCTPayload.description: The maximum size of the Common Transport (CT) payload including all CT headers but no FC frame headers, that may be sent or received by application software resident in the host containing this HBA. The unit is 32-bit words.

hh3cFdmiHbaPortTable.name: hh3cFdmiHbaPortTable
hh3cFdmiHbaPortTable.description: List of ports registered with Fabric Device Management Interface.

hh3cFdmiHbaPortEntry.name: hh3cFdmiHbaPortEntry
hh3cFdmiHbaPortEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table. It contains information about the Nx_port on the HBA, on the VSAN where the registration of the HBA with FDMI was received. If the HBA has registered some but not all of the information represented by the columnar objects in this table, then the value of the unregistered objects will be either the zero-length string (for string-based objects) or the zero value (for integer-based objects).

hh3cFdmiHbaPortId.name: hh3cFdmiHbaPortId
hh3cFdmiHbaPortId.reference: Fibre Channel Generic Services-6 Rev 9.4 Section 6.7.4.4.3.3 .

hh3cFdmiHbaPortSupportedFC4Type.name: hh3cFdmiHbaPortSupportedFC4Type
hh3cFdmiHbaPortSupportedFC4Type.reference: Fibre Channel Generic Services-6 Rev 9.4 Section 6.7.4.4.3.6 and Section 5.2.3.8 .
hh3cFdmiHbaPortSupportedFC4Type.description: The supported FC-4 types attribute registered for this port on this VSAN. This is an array of 256 bits (32 bytes). The order of the bits in the 256-bit (32-byte) value is represented in network-byte order. If no FC-4 types has been registered, then the value of this object is the zero-length string.

hh3cFdmiHbaPortSupportedSpeed.name: hh3cFdmiHbaPortSupportedSpeed
hh3cFdmiHbaPortSupportedSpeed.reference: Fibre Channel Generic Services-6 Rev 9.4 Section 6.7.4.4.3.8 .
hh3cFdmiHbaPortSupportedSpeed.description: The supported speed registered for this port on this VSAN. It is a bitmask that indicates the Fibre Channel Transmission Speeds that are supported on this port.

hh3cFdmiHbaPortCurrentSpeed.name: hh3cFdmiHbaPortCurrentSpeed
hh3cFdmiHbaPortCurrentSpeed.reference: Fibre Channel Generic Services-6 Rev 9.4 Section 6.7.4.4.3.9 .
hh3cFdmiHbaPortCurrentSpeed.description: The current speed registered for this port on this VSAN. It is a bitmask that indicates the Fibre Channel Transmission Speed at which this port is currently operating.

hh3cFdmiHbaPortMaxFrameSize.name: hh3cFdmiHbaPortMaxFrameSize
hh3cFdmiHbaPortMaxFrameSize.reference: Fibre Channel Generic Services-6 Rev 9.4 Section 6.7.4.4.3.10 .
hh3cFdmiHbaPortMaxFrameSize.description: The maximum frame size attribute registered for this port on this VSAN. The unit is bytes.

hh3cFdmiHbaPortOsDevName.name: hh3cFdmiHbaPortOsDevName
hh3cFdmiHbaPortOsDevName.reference: Fibre Channel Generic Services-6 Rev 9.4 Section 6.7.4.4.3.11 .
hh3cFdmiHbaPortOsDevName.description: The OS device name attribute registered for this port on this VSAN.

hh3cFdmiHbaPortHostName.description: The name of the host associated with this port.
